State-owned Industrial and Commercial Development Corporation has signed a deal with Standard Chartered Bank, giving buyers of its apartments in Mombasa favourable mortgage terms.Under the Memorandum of Understanding, the buyers of the Nyali-based Zamia Heights Apartments will enjoy a longer mortgage payment period of up to 25 years, meaning lower monthly repayments. &ldquo;The MoU will increase awareness and knowledge of Standard Chartered Bank mortgages and other banking solutions and ICDC solutions to a wide pool of clients and boost business for both organisations,&rdquo; ICDC acting executive director Kennedy Wanderi said in a statement.ICDC is targeting foreign visitors and multinationals attending business conferences at the coastal town.